<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-16381] use volatile to guarantee KafkaMetric#config visibility across threads</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-16381</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In KafkaMetirc.java, the getter is&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;```&lt;br/&gt;
@Override&lt;br/&gt;
public MetricName metricName() &lt;/p&gt;
{
return this.metricName;
}
&lt;p&gt;```&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and there is a setter&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;```&lt;br/&gt;
public void config(MetricConfig config) {&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; &#160; synchronized (lock) &lt;/p&gt;
{
&#160; &#160; this.config = config;
&#160; }
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since it&apos;s possible to set and get in the mean time, we should have lock in the getter as well&lt;/p&gt;</description>
